White House Press Secretary Jen Psaki provided several updates during a briefing. She mentioned that the US administered nearly 1.1 million COVID-19 vaccine shots, the highest single-day total since July 3. Psaki also noted that 50% of 12- to 17-year-olds have received at least one dose of the COVID-19 vaccine. Additionally, she announced that the Department of Health and Human Services will provide $85 million in funding to improve mental health services for children and youth. Psaki also addressed the situation in Afghanistan, stating that the Department of Homeland Security will coordinate the relocation of evacuated Afghans to the US. She confirmed that all evacuees will undergo COVID-19 testing and be offered vaccines upon arrival. Psaki also mentioned that President Biden and FEMA Administrator Deanne Criswell will host a call with the governors of Louisiana, Alabama, and Mississippi to discuss preparations for Tropical Storm Ida, which is expected to make landfall as a major hurricane.